content.description: A fantastic lay back crack with super easy road access.
content.location: This is the left route, inside the corner on the western most face. It is situated about 20' from the road.

climbs.name: Right Crack
climbs.fa: Potential Kent W and Rob Wagner

content.description:
This is the left facing corner that is just off the road above the pictograph panel. Not too much harder than the crack climb on the left.

The bottom is a little flakey but the rest is pretty good. 2 bolts for the anchor.

Apparently there are 2 more pitches above this. I havent climbed them. When i climbed it almost 2 years ago, straight up looked like a good option but traversing right might also work according to some comments.
content.protection: mostly hand sized pieces. I place a 5 in the pod towards the bottom.  60m easily reaches.
content.location:
Just around the corner, up canyon from the pictograph panel.

On the right side of the road if driving up canyon from the picto panel.

content.description:
Start up a left-facing flake, gain a bulge on good hands, and then move into the wide section. Enjoy a few body-lengths of OW climbing while admiring where others yarded on face features, only to send handfuls of choss down onto their belayer. Work up into a smaller crack in the back for the exit/finishing move. Clip the two bolt anchor from a nice ledge.

Take care when lowering - the thin crack at the exit move loves to pinch the rope and create a ton of drag.
content.protection: Single rack from .5 - #6. Could get by without the 5 or 6 but prob want one or the other.
content.location: Around the corner climbers left of Stephens Nielsons.
